            <p><add hand="#barker">Concerning house building.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Harrisburg </placeName><date when="1826-07-16">July 16th, 1826</date></p>
<p>Dear sir</p>

<p>I wrote to you by <persName>Mr. Givens</persName>, but he went by the way of the <placeName>Fort
settlement</placeName>, and it may be some time before you get the letter.</p>

<p>in our calculation of the cost of your <placeName>house</placeName>, we forgot the shingles,
and putting them on. Also my <persName>sawyers </persName>that I thought of getting had
taken a job for <persName>Vince</persName>, and it will be two or three weeks before they are
done, after which time I will send them on to you.</p>

<p>I wish you to instruct me what to do about the approaching 
election in case <persName>Harris </persName>does not return. I have put up the advertisements
according to your instructions. Let me here from you by <persName>Dr. Kenny</persName>.
My respects to <persName>Majr. Burnett</persName> and <persName>Mr- Williams</persName>, and believe me to be
yours &amp;.</p>

<p><persName>Saml C. Hirams</persName></p>

<p><persName>Col. Stephen F. Austin</persName>.</p>


        </div1>
